    <h1>Devex Job Posting Flow</h1>
    <p class="subtitle">Reading time 4 minutes</p>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>Project Overview</h2>
    <p>Devex is the go-to media platform for Global Development professionals. Along with their news pieces, they have other specialized products, including job postings focused on Global Development positions. In the last couple years, the amount of posted jobs has been decreasing.</p>
    <p>It was my task to analyze the state of job posting processes nowadays and come up with actionable proposals to <strong>improve the job posting flow to reduce drop-off during the process and increase engagement</strong>.</p>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>Discovery</h2>
    <p>We already knew that we had <strong>two different personas</strong> interacting with our job posting flow: big recruiters with expensive accounts that post jobs regularly and professionals from smaller organizations that post jobs per unit.</p>
    <p>We conducted a <strong>survey to gain insight</strong> from users who dropped-off of the process, but the response rate was very low.</p>
    <p>While we were waiting for the results of this survey, I continued research on two fronts:</p>
