    <p>There were many things we could do to improve our job posting process: from big drop off levels at the top of the funnel to lack of error prevention mechanisms through the posting process, amongst many functional bugs and many other issues.</p>
    <p>I met with the PO, Product VP and recruitment business stakeholders to share findings and agree on how much effort we wanted to put into this project and what changes we wanted to prioritize.</p>
  </section>
  
  <section>
    <h2>High level definition</h2>
    <p>I created a <strong>list of actionable items</strong> that we could implement to improve our process and divide them following the <strong>MoSCoW method</strong>. This prioritization was shared with the rest of the squad and we ordered them in a <strong>Risk vs Effort matrix</strong>, focusing on the technical implications for each item.</p>
